        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(channels): expose source actor attribution",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a generic `SourceActor` inbound context contract for the runtime identity of the message author.\n- Maps Signal sender identity into `SourceActor` without making the contract Signal-specific.\n- Documents that channel plugins should provide source actor attribution generically rather than hard-coding deployment-specific people or memory backends.\n\n## Stack\n\nThis is stacked after #96738 and `codex/signal-mention-facts-context`. Until those land, this PR's diff will include its dependencies.\n\n## Production impact\n\nNo behavior change by itself. The change gives prompts, tools, and memory integrations a stable way to distinguish a group participant from the operator/user.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/channels/inbound-event/context.test.ts extensions/signal/src/monitor/event-handler.mention-gating.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/openclaw-tools.plugin-context.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-utils.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/inbound-meta.test.ts extensions/memory-core/index.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/tools.citations.test.ts src/channels/inbound-event/context.test.ts extensions/signal/src/monitor/event-handler.mention-gating.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:prod`\n",
